env PAGER=cat man timing_path_based_exhaustive_enable_design_cover age
Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_path_b...esign_coverage(25.10)    timing_path_b...esign_coverage(25.10)

Name
       timing_path_based_exhaustive_enable_design_coverage

Syntax
       timing_path_based_exhaustive_enable_design_coverage

       {true | false}

       Default: false

       Enables  exhaustive  path-based analysis (PBA) to automatically pick up
       and analyze all the violating endpoints in the design, irrespective  of
       the specified maximum paths.

       When  set  to  true, exhaustive PBA analysis automatically picks up and
       analyzes the violating design endpoints instead of N endpoints  (speci-
       fied  with the report_timing -max_paths parameter). After analyzing the
       violating endpoints, the software reports the top N worst  endpoints  -
       depending on the specified value of N.

       When  set  to  false, exhaustive PBA analysis restricts analysis (using
       the -max_paths parameter) to the specified number of N endpoints.

       This global variable is valid for both EPBA as well as  infinite  depth
       path-based analysis (IPBA).

       Note: When this global variable is enabled, there may be an increase in
       run  time because the software will analyze all the violating endpoints
       and analysis will not be restricted to the specified N endpoints.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

